  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Expositor's Greek Testament",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Mark 15:44",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Omitted by Mt., whose narrative throughout is colourless compared with Mk.’s.—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "εἰ τέθνηκε",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ": ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "εἰ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " = ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ὅτι",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", after a verb of wonder (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "vide",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " Burton, M. and T., § 277, and Winer, § lx., 6).—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "εἰ ἀπέθανε",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ": ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "τέθνηκε",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " has reference to the present of the speaker, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἀπέθανε",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " to the moment of death.—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "πάλαι",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ": opposed to ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἄρτι",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", and not implying a considerable time before, but only bare priority to the present. Pilate’s question to the centurion was, did He die before now? = is He actually dead?",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Cambridge Bible for Schools and Colleges",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "44",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "And Pilate marvelled",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] Death by crucifixion did not generally supervene even for three days, and thirty-six hours is said to be the earliest period when it would be thus brought about. Pilate, therefore, marveled at the request of Joseph, and required the evidence of the centurion to assure himself of the fact.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
