  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Bengel's Gnomen",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Mark 15:44",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "Ἐθαύμασεν",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "marvelled",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") In fact, it was not the mere cross that deprived Jesus of life. [",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Those crucified sometimes used to protract life for a considerably longer time. Pilate had permitted the breaking of the legs; but the fact, that Jesus had died before the breaking of the legs (of the other two), came to Pilate’s knowledge through Joseph, and not until then",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".—V. g.]—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "πάλαι",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") Eustathius has showed that this word is used of even a rather short interval of time.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Pulpit Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verse 44.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "And Pilate marvelled if he were",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "already dead: and calling unto him the centurion, he asked him whether he had been any while dead.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " It must have Been somewhat early in the afternoon, probably not long after three o'clock, when Joseph went. The day being the Preparation, the Jews were anxious to satisfy the letter of the Law (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Deuteronomy 21:13",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), and that, more especially, because the coming sabbath was a \"high day.\" So they had gone early to Pilate to obtain permission to accelerate the deaths of the sufferers by the terrible additional punishment called ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "σκελοκοπία",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". This violence was not inflicted upon our Lord, because he was already dead; and so another Scripture was fulfilled, \"A bone of him shall not be broken.\" But it was necessary that Pilate should be assured of the fact that death had taken place before he gave up the body; and thus, in the providence of God, another evidence was given of the reality of Christ's death. Joseph   asked for the body (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "σῶμα",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). Then Pilate asked the centurion \"whether he had been any while dead.\" The verb here is in the aorist, and the adverb means \"formerly\" (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "εἰ πάλαι ἀπέθανε",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "); literally, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "if he died some time ago.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " Mark 15:44",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Vincent's Word Studies",
    "elements": [
